                            <container4_copy
                                cq:styleIds="[1653545825687,1653545847150,1653242825678,1653545835982]"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/container/v2/container">
                                <title2_copy_copy_cop
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545824678,1651545825668]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-10-29T12:16:38.194-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="Q: There’s a lot of buzz around genetic medicines, but how do they actually stack up against other therapeutic interventions?"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h5"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text2_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-10-29T12:16:46.772-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>The reason scientists like ours are excited about genetic medicine is because they have the potential to generate long-lasting effects in patients, and even potentially cure them, in a single treatment. This gives them an advantage over existing types of therapies, which often require multiple doses to maintain their effects.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>Compared to small molecules and biologics, genetic medicines also have the potential to reach a broader range of targets. While small molecules can reach inside or outside our cells to get to a target, because they’re fairly small, they’re not as effective at impacting targets with a large surface area.&amp;nbsp;Meanwhile, biotherapeutics like antibodies are sizable enough to bind to larger targets, but too large to penetrate cells.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                            </container4_copy>
                            <quote
                                cq:styleIds="[1000000000000]"
                                jcr:created="{Date}2024-10-29T12:16:55.274-04:00"
                                jcr:createdBy="VALENSX5"
                                jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-10-30T11:57:57.810-04:00"
                                jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/quote"
                                attributionName="Clark Pan, Ph.D. "
                                attributionTitle="VP, Biotherapeutics &amp; Genetic Medicine Technologies, AbbVie"
                                bgImageModifiers="resMode=sharp2&amp;op_sharpen=1"
                                fileReference="/content/dam/abbvie-com2/images/stories/generic-medicine/clark-pan-headshot.jpg"
                                imageModifiers="resMode=sharp2&amp;op_sharpen=1"
                                quote="With genetic medicine, we see a future where we can potentially cure patients."
                                quoteType="regular"
                                textSize="h0"/>
                            <container4_copy_copy
                                cq:styleIds="[1653545847150,1653242825678,1653545825687,1653545835982]"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/container/v2/container">
                                <text2_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-10-29T12:17:55.231-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>In contrast, genetic medicines can address targets inside and outside of cells, both large and small surfaces, and have the potential to do so with a higher degree of control or specificity.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>Scientists can use genetic medicine technologies to more precisely control biological effects by taking advantage of the different regulators to control the expression of genetic information. If, for example, we want to limit the expression of our genetic medicine to the brain, we can include, in our genetic medicine, a brain-specific promoter. That gives us another layer of specificity that would not be possible with other types of therapies.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                                <separator_copy_copy_
                                    cq:styleIds="[1662756423318]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-10-06T11:00:24.554-04:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-10-06T11:00:24.554-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/separator/v2/separator"/>
                                <title2_copy_copy_cop
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545824678,1651545825668]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-10-30T12:04:24.799-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="Q: What is AbbVie doing to advance the research and development of genetic medicines? "
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h5"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2024-10-29T15:11:25.931-04:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-10-30T12:04:56.776-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>We’ve made substantial investments in this area initially through collaborations. One is with REGENXBIO, where we’re working to develop an AAV gene therapy for eye diseases. We have also collaborated with Capsida to utilize their AAV engineering platform and manufacturing capability to identify and advance eye and neurodegenerative disease programs.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>Another collaboration we’ve invested in, with Umoja Biopharma, focuses on developing novel CAR-T cell therapies in oncology.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>Through our collaborations, we’re seeking to address current challenges using genetic medicine concepts.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>What’s also unique about AbbVie is that, not only do we look for partners, but we also invest in the ecosystem. Through our venture arm, we are investing in many novel technologies for genetic medicines while also looking out for strategic partnerships that can really move these technologies forward.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                            </container4_copy_copy>
                            <quote_copy
                                cq:styleIds="[1000000000000]"
                                jcr:created="{Date}2024-10-29T12:16:55.274-04:00"
                                jcr:createdBy="VALENSX5"
                                jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-10-30T11:58:04.734-04:00"
                                jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/quote"
                                attributionName="Clark Pan, Ph.D. "
                                attributionTitle="VP, Biotherapeutics &amp; Genetic Medicine Technologies, AbbVie"
                                bgImageModifiers="resMode=sharp2&amp;op_sharpen=1"
                                fileReference="/content/dam/abbvie-com2/images/stories/generic-medicine/clark-pan-headshot.jpg"
                                imageModifiers="resMode=sharp2&amp;op_sharpen=1"
                                quote="With our strong foundation in biotherapeutics and small molecules, and willingness to invest in cutting-edge technology, we are poised to make a positive impact on patients with genetic medicines."
                                quoteType="regular"
                                textSize="h0"/>
                            <container4_copy_copy_1716637703
                                cq:styleIds="[1653545847150,1653242825678,1653545825687,1653545835982]"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/container/v2/container">
                                <title2_copy_copy_cop
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545824678,1651545825668]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-10-29T12:19:55.857-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="Q: Why is AbbVie well positioned to do this work? What contributions do you bring to the field? "
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h5"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text2_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-10-29T12:20:05.756-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>Our strategic investments, partnerships, and strong foundation in biologics, precision medicine, and complex diseases position us to make significant advances in genetic medicines. We have led therapeutic innovations in fields like ADCs (antibody drug conjugates) in oncology.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>Our deep expertise in biotherapeutics and chemistry, and a talent pool of experts in the field, has propelled us to become a leading ADC company. Similarly, our strong foundation in biotherapeutics and small molecules, willingness to invest in cutting-edge technologies, and our ability to attract and nurture world-class scientific talent will help us advance the field of genetic medicines as a leader.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                                <separator_copy_copy_
                                    cq:styleIds="[1662756423318]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-10-06T11:00:24.554-04:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-10-06T11:00:24.554-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/separator/v2/separator"/>
                                <title2_copy_copy_cop_1738568522
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545824678,1651545825668]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-10-29T12:20:44.977-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="Q: How do you envision the future of genetic medicines 10 to 20 years from now?"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h5"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text2_copy_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-10-29T12:20:55.282-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>While it's very transformational, most of the clinical successes we’ve seen with genetic medicine have been limited to rare diseases.&amp;nbsp;While that has a great impact, our vision for the future is to unleash the full potential of genetic medicine. It’s our vision within the next 10 years to see, through our investment and hard work that genetic medicine will have broader applications.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>With genetic medicine, we also see a future where we can potentially cure patients, rather than manage their symptoms. That’s our vision for the future and we really believe genetic medicine&amp;nbsp;has the potential to get there.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                                <separator_copy_copy__504111190
